  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.7.2-stable\r\nGit Commit: 1db4ecdc0b9e828ff65777fb466fc7c1d04e0de9\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.9\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=/usr/lib/go-1.9\r\n\r\nI am trying to send about 50 transactions from one account to other accounts sequentially, i have set nonce to \"web3.eth.getTransactionCount(myaddress, 'pending') in every transaction before call sendTransaction.\r\nMy test in ropsten net is fairly well, but got error in main net:\r\n_Error: Returned error: replacement transaction underpriced_\r\nAnd I also notice that in the geth console, the return of getTransactionCount just dropped, i guest that maybe the problem.\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7152596/35569998-ca99d9ba-0608-11e8-96d4-b8f6ff7b6ef6.png)\r\nAnd now, at this time I am writing this issue, the largest nonce is 629 in a pending transaction in etherscan([here](https://etherscan.io/tx/0x7e2348db85a288989fa99c496c4ec74ccfeff04d8c3469d45bb05cce5c303bf8)),\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7152596/35570848-531786fa-060b-11e8-943e-4d7c3ff6781a.png)\r\n\r\n but the largest nonce in my geth node(which i am sure is update to the newest) is 592:\r\n_> eth.getTransactionCount('0x2592a20db4c16c89b08e301792953911c4751d7f', 'pending')\r\n592_\r\n\r\nI just don't know how to explain this, and not sure if this is a bug, especially the same run fairly well in ropsten testnet.\r\nAny help will be very appreciated.\r\n",
