    "body": "Pending transaction count is the \"nonce\" after executing the pending block. However the pending block doesn't contain **all** pending transactions, just the ones that fit into the next block. If the miner computes a different pending block, you might have a different pending nonce afterwards. \r\n\r\nIf you want to submit many transactions, then it's better to retrieve the nonce ones, and afterwards manage it yourself.",
